*The course focuses on the development of the post-Cold War international order, placing it in the context of earlier transformations in the international system. 
*It brings the perspectives of East-Central Europe, the Baltic States and the Nordic states into focus.
*The objective is to offer the student background knowledge and the tools to think about the meanings of current international developments. Are we currently witnessing another tranformation in the international order?Objectives/eesmärkid:  The purpose of the course is to analyse and conceptualise basic events, developments and trends in contemporary international relations (since the end of the Cold War) from the perspective of the main schools of foreign-policy analysis and international relations theory.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  After passing the course student -can describe the main events, developments and trends in contemporary international relations -knows and is able to use the main methods of Foreign Policy Analysis -knows the main schools of the international relations theory -can analyse the main developements in international politics affecting the contemporary history of Estonia.
